correctness.rationale: Extensive schema and factual errors. Schema violations: multiple fields use nulls or placeholders (e.g., plasmaPower: null; supercycleDesign: null; growthPerCycle.value.numericValue: null; numberofCycles.numericValue: null; uniformity/conformality/roughness/filmDensity numericValue: null; dosingTime/purgeTime/flowRates are empty arrays). Required materialProperties subfields are populated with nulls or speculative values (filmComposition.atomicRatio set to 1:1 without support). Use of 'Not Found' in many string fields (carrierGas, purgingGas, reactor, deliveryMethod, safety, etc.) breaks the no-empty/traceability requirement. Structural issues: filmThickness is duplicated and placed inside growthPerCycle against the schema; plasmaPower and supercycleDesign should be omitted if not used rather than set to null. Factual/unit errors: resistivity reported as 1.2 Ω·m instead of ~1.2×10^-4 Ω·m (1.2×10^-2 Ω·cm in the article); carrierDensity set to 4.9 with unit C-PER-M3 instead of ~4.9×10^21 PER-M3 (converted from 4.9×10^15 cm^-3); subthresholdSwing recorded as 1.7 mV instead of 1.7 V/dec (should be 1700 mV if using the schema’s MilliV unit); onOffRatio given as 7.3 instead of 7.3×10^4; materialProperties.mobility = 1.63 cm^2/Vs is a device FE mobility, not a Hall mobility; atomicRatio 1:1 is not reported in the article; substrate text contains incorrect units (“V cm” instead of Ω·cm). Missing data: no dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC, number of cycles, optical properties, uniformity/conformality, roughness, film density—yet these fields are required by the schema or are populated with invalid placeholders. Overall, the extraction is neither schema-compliant nor traceable for many fields and contains several incorrect values and units. Correct the units/magnitudes, remove placeholders/nulls, and supply only article-supported values aligned with the schema.

completeness.rationale: Major completeness and schema-compliance gaps. Numerous required fields are empty, null, or populated with placeholders, and several values/units do not match the article. Specific issues: (1) Missing/empty required processParameters: dosingTime [], purgeTime [], flowRates [], nucleationPeriod.numericValue = null, thicknessControl.growthPerCycle.value.numericValue = null, thicknessControl.numberofCycles.numericValue = null, saturation set to False without support. (2) reactantSelection: carrierGas and purgingGas set to 'Not Found' (placeholders, not traceable to the article). (3) Invalid/unsupported nulls: plasmaPower = null, supercycleDesign = null. (4) Material properties required by schema are largely missing or null: uniformity.variation.numericValue = null; conformality.aspectRatio.numericValue = null; filmComposition.elementalConcentration.values.numericValue = null; filmComposition.atomicRatio set to '1:1' (not reported in the article); crystallinity not provided; roughness.value.numericValue = null; filmDensity.value.numericValue = null. (5) Device properties/units inconsistent with article and schema: onOffRatio numericValue should be 7.3e4 (not 7.3); subthresholdSwing unit is set to mV but value 1.7 corresponds to 1.7 V/decade—should be encoded as 1700 mV if schema mandates mV; fieldEffectMobility/thresholdVoltage only captured for one condition while the article reports multiple plasma exposure times (0, 2.5, 5, 7.5 min) with different values—these variations are not represented. (6) Film electrical properties mis-specified: resistivity entered as 1.2 Ω·m vs article 1.2×10^-2 Ω·cm; carrierDensity entered as 4.9 (C-PER-M3) vs article 4.9×10^15 cm^-3; mobility 1.63 cm^2/V·s appears to be device msat, not Hall mobility of the film. (7) Several fields contain 'Not Found' strings which are not traceable scientific values (reactor details, deliveryMethod, opticalProperties.characterizationMethod, etc.). To improve completeness: populate carrier/purging gases; provide dosing/purge times, flow rates, GPC or at least number of cycles; correct all units and magnitudes (resistivity, carrier density, SS, on/off ratio); remove nulls or fill with article-supported values; either represent each plasma-treatment condition as separate processes or clearly scope deviceProperties to the as-deposited state and reflect all reported device metrics consistently with the article.
